      <hedline>
        <hl1>Who's at Fault for Failing Schools?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jack Linder letter on unfairness of putting entire burden of education of teachers and schools; points out parents' role in educating their children (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''What Rudy Crew Didn't Do'' (Op-Ed, Dec. 29), by Sol Stern: To put the entire burden of education on the schools and the teachers is unfair. What about the parents' role in educating their children? Without the parents, the education process is incomplete.</p>
        <p>JACK LINDER  New York, Dec. 29, 1999</p>
      </block>
